  "text": "Multiple cellular stressors, including activation of the tumour suppressor p53, can stimulate autophagy [CITATION_1] . Pharmacological inhibition, knockout or knockdown of p53 can induce autophagy [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Cytoplasmic but not nuclear p53 is responsible for autophagy inhibition [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . However, the upstream signals controlling cytoplasmic p53 are still unknown. How cytoplasmic p53 influences chemotherapy through autophagy also needs to be explored.",
